creator: Mindshift Dev
descriptionHtml:
A note from the developer
I, the developer of this app, have struggled with anxiety and negative thought patterns throughout my life. I often felt unhappy and my anxiety stopped me from doing the things I want. Until recently I never considered seeking help. I just waited and hoped for an epiphany that would change the way I am. Unfortunately, this never happened so I decided to visit a psychologist.

Talking to a psychologist helped me a lot and I strongly encourage you to seek a psychologist if you are feeling down for a considerable amount of time. Mindshift contains a collection of insights and exercises that I found helpful in the sessions with my psychologist. It helped me understand what was wrong with my mindset and how to think differently. I hope it will benefit you too, and that you feel better with time.

About Mindshift
This app contains a collection of insights and daily exercises about common negative thought patterns. This includes exercises based on cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT). The insights are designed to give you an understanding of how a negative mind works and how to change to a more positive mindset. The exercises let you put these insights into practice.

The aim is to do these exercises regularly, preferably every day. You also have to set your happiness level. When the day is over, the app automatically saves your exercises and stores them in your history. This results in a diary of challenged thought patterns. It should provide insights into your common negative thought patterns. And if the exercises work for you, you should gradually feel happier.

Good luck in making a positive mindshift!

title: Mindshift

creator: Mindshift Dev
descriptionHtml:
This app is made by me, a software developer struggling with social anxiety and negative thought patterns. The exercises and insights in this app are inspired by sessions with my psychologist.

With Mindshift you can:
* Do thought exercises everyday
* Learn how to shift negative thought patterns
* Learn how to increase your happiness
* Track your happiness
* Meditate using a timer

The exercises and insights in this app are based on cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT). The insights are designed to give you an understanding of how a negative mind works and how to change to a more positive mindset. The exercises let you put these insights into practice.

The aim is to do these exercises regularly, preferably every day. This results in a diary of challenged thought patterns. Make sure to set your happiness level after doing the exercises. A change in your happiness level should indicate if the exercises work for you.

Good luck in making a positive mindshift!

Privacy
Nothing you write down will ever be shared with anyone. Mindshift does not require an internet connection. Data is stored in a simple database file on your phone. Google’s default Auto Backup feature, a feature that automatically backs up app data in your Google Drive account, is disabled. To erase your data stored in the local database file, simply uninstall the app. Mindshift does not require any permissions except for Google’s billing service which is needed for making in-app purchases.


If you have any comments or ideas to improve the app, feel free to email me at: mindshiftdeveloper@gmail.com

About Mindshift
The exercises and insights in this app are based on cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT). The insights are designed to give you an understanding of how a negative mind works and how to change to a more positive mindset. The exercises allow you to put these insights into practice.

The aim is to do these exercises regularly, preferably every day. The result is a diary of challenged thought patterns. Be sure to measure your happiness level after doing the exercises. A change in your happiness level should indicate whether the exercises are working for you.

Good luck in making a positive mindshift!

Privacy
Nothing you write will ever be shared with anyone. Mindshift does not need an internet connection. Data is stored in an encrypted database file on your phone. Google's default auto-backup feature, which automatically backs up app data to your Google Drive account, is disabled. To delete your data stored in the local database file, simply uninstall the app. Mindshift requires no permissions other than Google's billing service, which is required for in-app purchases.


Feel free to email me if you have any comments or ideas for improving the app: mindshiftdeveloper@gmail.com
